cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with face recognition and super-resolution using neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of multiple frames and sub-pixel movements suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The neural network architecture and training process involve optimization and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the alignment problem mentioned in the abstract suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
